  draftWording:
    '17.4  Where the Hospital achieves performance at or better than the top quartile of the Schedule 3 benchmarks for four consecutive Quarters, the rates in Schedule 1 will be increased by an additional 0.5% at the next indexation event ("Quality Loading"). The Quality Loading applies for the following 12 months and renews on the same test. Determination is by reference to the quarterly reports already provided under clause 17.2, with any dispute resolved under clause 18.',
  rationale:
    'Quality currently carries only downside under this Agreement (cl. 17.3 makes adverse variance a breach trigger while attaching nothing to excellence). Bayview has delivered top-quartile results for eight consecutive quarters — performance the Fund already markets to members. A 0.5% loading converts a proven member benefit into a priced term, using reporting that already exists, at a cost of ~$15.6k/yr against a $3.1m base.',
  financialImpact: '+$15.6k/yr at current volumes; self-funding for the Fund if it retains even ~7 members/yr through reduced complaints and waits.',
